    <instructions>Whip cream cheese until smooth.  Add in mayonnaise, sour cream, and garlic salt.  Whip until smooth.  Stir in remaining ingredients.  Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes, or until ready to serve.

Bought Trader Joe’s house brand mayonnaise, which according to a web thread is the locally-available brand that is the most like Duke's Mayonnaise (a southern brand used in the south to make Pimiento Cheese.

Cheeses used were also from Trader Joe’s - a New York X-tra sharp orange cheddar (yummy!) and a Canadian X-tra sharp white cheddar (SUPER yummy!).  May need to add extra mayonnaise for creaminess, and blend quite a while to reduce the small, hard cheese chunks.</instructions>
